Finally watched The Secret Agent on flight home. An indie Brazil movie that cleaned up at Cannes last year(13min standing ovation). I get why, it's incredible. Layered characters, slowly unfolding plot, writing that has a POV but w/ out lecturing. But really it’s the photography/locations/wardrobe etc that are so detailed it fully immerses you into 1970s Brazil. Must have taken an insane amt of work to make this film. I give it a 9.5/10.

